#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:1
msgid "_as_float_vector"
msgstr "_as_float_vector"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:14
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:16
msgid ""
"Normalizza un input numerico in un array `float64` monodimensionale e finito. E il check di base "
"su cui si appoggiano piu moduli del package."
msgstr ""
"Normalizes a numeric input into a one-dimensional, finite `float64` array. It is the base check "
"used by multiple package modules."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:18
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:20
msgid "`values` deve poter essere convertito da `numpy.asarray(..., dtype=float)`."
msgstr "`values` must be convertible with `numpy.asarray(..., dtype=float)`."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:21
msgid "Il risultato deve essere monodimensionale."
msgstr "The result must be one-dimensional."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:22
msgid "Se `allow_empty=False`, l'array non puo essere vuoto."
msgstr "If `allow_empty=False`, the array cannot be empty."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:23
msgid "Tutti gli elementi devono essere finiti."
msgstr "All elements must be finite."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:25
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:27
msgid ""
"internamente da quasi tutte le funzioni pubbliche di "
"[`stats_utils`](../../moduli/stats_utils/index.md)"
msgstr "internally by almost all public functions in [`stats_utils`](../../moduli/stats_utils/index.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:28
msgid "in [`histogram`](../../moduli/plot_utils/histogram.md)"
msgstr "in [`histogram`](../../moduli/plot_utils/histogram.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:29
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md)"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:31
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "Failure modes"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:33
msgid "`ValueError` se l'input non e monodimensionale"
msgstr "`ValueError` if the input is not one-dimensional"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:34
msgid "`ValueError` se l'input e vuoto quando non ammesso"
msgstr "`ValueError` if the input is empty when that is not allowed"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:35
msgid "`ValueError` se sono presenti `NaN` o infiniti"
msgstr "`ValueError` if `NaN` values or infinities are present"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:37
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it stays private"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/as-float-vector.md:39
msgid ""
"E un dettaglio infrastrutturale condiviso. Documentarla aiuta a capire il package, ma esporla "
"come API pubblica vincolerebbe inutilmente l'implementazione interna."
msgstr ""
"It is a shared infrastructure detail. Documenting it helps explain the package, but exposing it "
"as a public API would unnecessarily constrain the internal implementation."

